This paper deals with the problem of learning high-quality word embeddings, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) research. The use of attention mechanisms is also a common technique in NLP, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of embeddings is also relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method involves tasks related to information retrieval, which is relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
